         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">May 1 /82. ¶ Dear Baron ¶  ¶ At your suggestion ¶  I wrote to Profr. Pfeffer for Gartners  ¶ Forstera ¶  alias  ¶ Athecia ¶ , it is Royena glabra with the fruit turned upside down. Curiously enough Fo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.05.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS embossed with crest of Royal Gardens Kew.</p>
               </note>May 1 /82.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At your suggestion<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See W. Pfeffer to M, 26 October 1881, and M to J. Hooker, 12 December 1881.</p>
               </note> I wrote to Profr. Pfeffer for Gartners <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Forstera">Forstera</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> alias <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Athecia</hi>
               </seg>, it is <name key="Royena%20glabra">Royena glabra</name> with the fruit turned upside down. Curiously enough Forsters original ticket with <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Royena</hi>
               </seg>? <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">glabra</hi>
               </seg> is with the specimen. This was stuck inside the lid of the little box &amp; unobserved till after we named the plant I have returned it to Mr Pfeffer.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos D Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
